Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 692
S.P. 309 In Senate, February 25, 2025
Messaging
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee
on Education and Cultural Affairs pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator PIERCE of Cumberland.
Cosponsored by Representative CLOUTIER of Lewiston and
Senators: DUSON of Cumberland, LIBBY of Cumberland, RAFFERTY of York,
Representative: BRENNAN of Portland.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
3 allocations are made.
4 PUBLIC BROADCASTING CORPORATION, MAINE
5 Maine Public Broadcasting Corporation 0033
6 Initiative: Provides additional ongoing funds to align state funding more closely with the
7 statutory requirement to provide emergency broadcast messaging for public safety.
8 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
9 All Other $350,000 $350,000
10 __________ __________
11 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $350,000 $350,000
12
8 SUMMARY
139 This bill provides additional ongoing funds to align state funding more closely with the
1140 statutory requirement to provide emergency broadcast messaging for public safety.
